# Nen MCP Tool Usage Guidelines

This guide helps the AI assistant understand **when** and **how** to use Nen Platform MCP tools during workflow authoring.

## ⚠️ PREREQUISITE: API Key Required

**All Nen MCP tools require a valid API key to function.** Without it, every MCP tool call (`nen_run`, `nen_update_workflow`, `nen_get_run_logs`, etc.) will fail with an authentication error.

**If a user tries to use any MCP tool and it fails, check whether they have set up their API key first.**

### How to set up the API key:
1. Obtain your Nen API key from the Nen platform/dashboard
2. Open `~/.cursor/mcp.json` and ensure it contains the following (merge into the existing `mcpServers` object if one already exists):

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "Nen Platform": {
      "url": "https://mcp.getnen.ai/v1",
      "headers": {
        "x-api-key": "YOUR_API_KEY_HERE"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**Tell the user this upfront if they haven't set up their API key yet.** Do not attempt to run workflows or call any MCP tools until the user confirms their API key is configured.

